Duke Stroud https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duke_Stroud 0 Duke Summer Stroud (born April 14, 1938) is an American actor who has appeared on screen since the 1970s. He is the brother of actor Don Stroud. His first credited role came in 1973 when he appeared in as Jameson in an episode of Mission: Impossible. He has also appeared in TV serials including The Dukes of Hazzard, Voyagers!, The Outlaws, Hill Street Blues, Law Order and Human Desires. He also appeared in several films which include The Long Riders, Zoot Suit, Top Gun and most recently Beautiful Dreamer. He also played Vince McKinnon on NBC's daytime soap opera Another World.
